rms.model

Class Users

  • java.lang.Object
    • rms.model.Users

  • public class Users
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is meant to be used with the PRMS database. It is a model class for a user for the users table in the database.

    • Field Detail

      • userId

        private int userId
        int that represents the identification of a user. This value is unique in the PRMS database.

      • userName

        private java.lang.String userName
        String that represents the username or login credentials of a user. This value should be unique in the database.

      • userEmail

        private java.lang.String userEmail
        String that represents the email or login credentials of a user. This value should be unique in the database and verified to see if email actually exists.

      • userPassword

        private java.lang.String userPassword
        String that represents the password of a user. The value passed into this variable should be hashed.

      • userType

        private int userType
        int that represents the type of user. Types of users include 1=Super User 2=Basic User 3=Manager

      • userPhone

        private java.lang.String userPhone
        String that represents the phone number of the user. The current format of these numbers is: 123-456-7890

      • locationId

        private int locationId
        int that represents the location id of the user. This is mapped to the locations table to get more information on the location of the user.

      • first_name

        private java.lang.String first_name
        String that represents the first name of the user.

      • last_name

        private java.lang.String last_name
        String that represents the last name of the user.

        Constructor that constructs a user when all information for the user is present.
        Parameters:
        userId - int that represents the identification of a user. This value is unique in the PRMS database.
        userName - String that represents the username or login credentials of a user. This value should be unique in the database.
        userEmail - String that represents the email or login credentials of a user. This value should be unique in the database and verified to see if email actually exists.
        userPassword - String that represents the password of a user. The value passed into this variable should be hashed.
        userType - int that represents the type of user. Types of users include 1=Super User 2=Basic User 3=Manager
        userPhone - String that represents the phone number of the user. The current format of these numbers is: 123-456-7890
        locationId - int that represents the location id of the user. This is mapped to the locations table to get more information on the location of the user.
        first_name - String that represents the first name of the user.
        last_name - String that represents the last name of the user.
